In this statement, President Obama expresses his pride and gratitude for the launch of the Space Shuttle Atlantis and the dedicated workers who have contributed to America's Space Shuttle program. He recognizes that while this may be the final flight of the Space Shuttle, it marks the beginning of a new era in space exploration. The President emphasizes the importance of advancing science and technology, enhancing knowledge and education, promoting innovation and economic growth, and setting ambitious goals for space exploration, including sending Americans to Mars. He congratulates Atlantis and its crew on a successful launch and wishes them luck on their mission to the International Space Station. Finally, he expresses his pride in the accomplishments of the American space program and his excitement for the future of space exploration.